textDelta: What is active listening? And how can I be more actively engaged when I’m listening to someone? Active listening means fully concentrating on what the other person is saying. It means listening with your ears, eyes, mind and heart. It means giving your full attention to the other person. Many people think that listening means waiting for the other person to stop talking so that you can talk. But true listening means giving the other person your full attention. When you listen actively, you show that you really care about what the other person is saying. You listen with your heart as well as your ears. You show the other person that what she’s saying is important to you. Active listening requires patience. You listen without interrupting. You listen

What age group has the highest death rate from AIDS? A: Quick Answer The age group with the highest death rate from AIDS is 45 to 54, according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. As of 2012, this age group accounted for 13.3 percent of all AIDS deaths. Keep Learning According to the CDC, 1.2 million Americans are living with HIV/AIDS, and 56,300 Americans died from AIDS in 2012.
